-- EUROPE RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Deutsche Bank, SSE, Air France 
-- 
-- Mon Dec 22, 2014 03:07AM EST
-- None



Dec 22 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several European companies, including Air France and Deutsche Bank, on Monday.

HIGHLIGHTS * SSE <SSE.L>: HSBC cuts to neutral from overweight; target price to 1810p from 1830p * Air France <AIRF.PA>: SocGen, HSBC raise target price on the stock * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: Citigroup cuts target to 34 euros from 36 euros; rating buyFollowing is a summary of research actions on European companies reported by Reuters on Monday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order.* Air France <AIRF.PA>: HSBC raises target price to 10 euros from 9 euros; rating overweight * Air France <AIRF.PA>: SocGen raises target price to 7.8 euros from 6.7 euros; rating hold * Atos <ATOS.PA>: UBS raises target price to 70 euros from 61 euros; rating buy * BBVA <BBVA.MC>: Citigroup cuts target price to 8.50 euros from 9.20 euros; rating neutral * Continental <CONG.DE>: Goldman Sachs cuts target to 193 euros from 195 euros; rating buy * Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE>: Citigroup cuts target to 34 euros from 36 euros; rating buy * Gedeon Richter <GDRB.BU>: Jefferies cuts target price to huf 3100; rating underperform * Grupo Catalana Occidente <GCO.MC>: JP Morgan raises target to 29 euros from 28.10 euros * Krka <KRKG.LJ>: Jefferies cuts target price to 57 euros; rating hold * Neste Oil <NES1V.HE>: UBS raises target price to 20 euros from 19.50 euros; rating neutral * SAS AB <SAS.ST>: HSBC cuts to neutral from overweight * SSE <SSE.L>: HSBC cuts to neutral from overweight; target price to 1810p from 1830p